Ask HN: Best open-source projects to learn from?
text:
What are the best open-source projects / snippets of code that caught your attention? I understand that there are different criteria when someone classify something as best / beautiful. I mean below properties when I mention the word 'best' -

a) Solves a real problem b) Relatively easier to understand c) Relatively easier to modify / extend d) Relatively easier to test e) Has seen an evolutionary curve over time

I make my living by writing code for past few years & feel like reaching out to the best folks in the industry for their insights.

text:
When asked about good or phenomenal books, computer scientists and programmers recommend books like SICP, K&R, etc. The thing is they are old (not a bad thing) and have stood the test of time.

But aren't people writing good books anymore? Why aren't newer books delivering the same value as those giants?

Ask HN: What do you wish you knew about your customers/users?
text:
What piece of information about your users would change your product and how would it change it if you knew it right now?

eg. Knowing that people would be willing to pay $x rather than $y for your pro plan

Knowing if they were a student or a professional might alter your landing page content or might result in different plans being suggested.
